It’s understood a bakkie and a delivery vehicle collided. Passengers seated at the back of both vehicles sustained minor injuries. JOHANNESBURG - Authorities are investigating the circumstances surrounding a crash in which 21 people were injured on the R21 near Kempton Park on Thursday morning. It’s understood a bakkie and a delivery vehicle collided. Passengers seated at the back of both vehicles sustained minor injuries. ER24's Russel Meiring says: "Paramedics immediately assessed the patients and they found that 21 people had sustained minor to moderate injuries. "Fortunately no serious injuries or fatalities were found on the scene. The patients were treated for their injuries and were transported to various hospitals for further care."